WEBVTT

00:01.421 --> 00:03.336
<i>Previously on</i> Lucifer...

00:03.371 --> 00:05.336
You're the Lord of Hell,
for crying out loud.

00:05.371 --> 00:07.842
I'm retired, Maze. I've
got nothing but time.

00:07.877 --> 00:08.986
How could you possibly help me?

00:09.021 --> 00:12.296
I have the ability to draw
out people's forbidden desires.

00:12.331 --> 00:13.729
I got it. The name,

00:13.764 --> 00:14.793
the whole Lucifer thing,

00:14.828 --> 00:16.062
and desire's like your superpower.

00:16.097 --> 00:17.463
It's more like a gift from God, really.

00:17.498 --> 00:19.971
I saw Lucifer do some
things that I can't explain.

00:20.006 --> 00:21.713
Is Lucifer a magician?

00:21.748 --> 00:23.915
That's sort of what I'm
trying to figure out.

00:23.950 --> 00:27.335
You were once the brightest
of all of God's angels.

00:27.370 --> 00:30.287
And now, your time here on Earth

00:30.322 --> 00:31.788
is affecting you, dear brother.

00:31.823 --> 00:32.807
You're changing.

00:32.842 --> 00:34.475
My life is change.

00:34.510 --> 00:38.016
- What are you doing here?
- Ooh, how's your ex? Detective Douche?

00:38.051 --> 00:40.325
You like working with
the detective, don't you?

00:40.360 --> 00:42.236
I told you, I'm good at punishing people.

00:42.271 --> 00:44.791
Nay, I'm the best at punishing bad people.

00:44.826 --> 00:48.841
Yeah, well, I think you don't
just enjoy punishing the bad guys.

00:48.876 --> 00:53.498
I think you're starting to like
seeking justice for the good ones.

00:55.775 --> 00:58.009
♪ ♪

01:01.858 --> 01:06.719
♪ The trees stood like knives ♪

01:06.754 --> 01:13.024
♪ And claimed us for their own ♪

01:13.059 --> 01:19.520
♪ I'm sold down the river ♪

01:19.555 --> 01:25.909
♪ Before I knew I had enough ♪

01:25.978 --> 01:27.274
♪ Before I knew ♪

01:27.356 --> 01:30.957
- (gunshot)
- ♪ I'd sink deeper ♪

01:32.352 --> 01:36.755
♪ Than where you'll stop... ♪

01:37.517 --> 01:39.859
(grunting)

01:39.894 --> 01:41.270
He's the Devil!

01:41.305 --> 01:43.388
<i>He's the Devil!</i>

01:43.658 --> 01:44.789
♪ Stop ♪

01:44.824 --> 01:47.592
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

01:50.027 --> 01:50.795
♪ Stop ♪

01:50.830 --> 01:54.098
♪ Stop, stop, stop. ♪

01:56.214 --> 01:58.347
(clattering)

02:09.149 --> 02:11.382
♪ ♪

02:26.032 --> 02:27.098
- (thump)
- (gasps)

02:27.133 --> 02:28.566
Lucifer?

02:29.793 --> 02:30.808
Well,

02:30.843 --> 02:33.017
good morning, Detective.

02:35.435 --> 02:37.478
What the hell are you doing here?

02:37.513 --> 02:39.912
- Setting the table.
- You broke into my house?

02:39.947 --> 02:41.531
Yes, well, I hope you don't
mind, but I made a little brekkie.

02:41.566 --> 02:43.576
You were taking forever in the shower.

02:43.836 --> 02:45.451
What do you do in there?

02:45.486 --> 02:46.943
You are unbelievable!

02:46.978 --> 02:50.008
Oh, thank you, but it's you
who should take the compliment.

02:50.043 --> 02:52.509
Really kept things up since <i>Hot
Tub High School,</i> haven't we?

02:52.544 --> 02:53.437
Ding-dong.

02:53.472 --> 02:55.369
(sighs) I want to shoot you.

02:55.404 --> 02:56.761
Tease. Do it.

02:56.796 --> 02:57.982
I'm immortal, remember?

02:58.017 --> 03:00.062
Uh, do you have any truffle oil?

03:00.164 --> 03:02.354
Lucifer, get out of my house now.

03:02.389 --> 03:04.182
- We haven't eaten yet.
- Out.

03:04.217 --> 03:05.812
Well, don't we need to
discuss the next case?

03:05.847 --> 03:07.689
There is no next case.

03:07.724 --> 03:08.651
- What?
- Out.

03:08.686 --> 03:10.296
We're already late, so let's go.

03:10.331 --> 03:11.268
Lucifer!

03:11.303 --> 03:12.835
Yeah.

03:12.870 --> 03:14.281
What in God's name are you doing here?

03:14.316 --> 03:16.280
Nothing in his name.
Here on my own, actually.

03:16.316 --> 03:18.817
BEATRICE: Did you and
Mommy have a sleepover?

03:18.852 --> 03:21.784
CHLOE: No. No. Absolutely not, no.

03:21.819 --> 03:23.924
What are you guys doing here anyway?

03:24.049 --> 03:25.928
She left her bird report here.

03:25.963 --> 03:27.692
- BEATRICE: Want to see?
- Um, not really.

03:27.727 --> 03:29.916
Here, have a snack, child.

03:31.667 --> 03:33.816
Are you sleeping with this idiot?

03:33.917 --> 03:36.518
She hasn't had the
pleasure, unfortunately, no.

03:37.170 --> 03:39.328
Okay, everybody out.
Trixie has to get to school.

03:39.363 --> 03:41.669
I got to get to work. Come on, out, please.

03:41.704 --> 03:44.411
No, no, no, no, no, you
can't throw me out again.

03:44.550 --> 03:45.676
Again?

03:45.796 --> 03:47.011
So this is a habit.

03:47.047 --> 03:48.630
- Yes, shocking, isn't it?
- No.

03:48.665 --> 03:50.498
Never been thrown out of
anywhere before in my life.

03:50.533 --> 03:52.250
Well, except for Heaven, of course.

03:53.420 --> 03:55.601
Fine, fine, fine, fine.

03:55.636 --> 03:58.055
But somebody please flip the
omelet if it's not already ruined.

03:58.090 --> 03:59.791
Hey, Dan, I'm...

04:00.119 --> 04:01.526
Really, Chloe?

04:02.228 --> 04:04.262
I'm disappointed in you.

04:07.991 --> 04:10.758
♪ Oh ♪

04:10.904 --> 04:13.971
♪ Oh, oh ♪

04:14.007 --> 04:17.175
♪ Oh ♪

04:17.209 --> 04:20.178
♪ Oh, oh ♪

04:20.213 --> 04:22.264
♪ Black is the Devil,
dark is the night... ♪

04:22.339 --> 04:23.476
Good. Right, you're here.

04:23.511 --> 04:24.906
- Um, I need to chat.
- Lucifer, we don't have an appointment.

04:24.941 --> 04:26.440
Something very disturbing's just happened.

04:26.475 --> 04:28.006
It's horrific, really.

04:28.041 --> 04:30.568
Uh, for the second time,

04:30.603 --> 04:31.907
I've been thrown out of a woman's house.

04:31.942 --> 04:33.725
- Okay, sorry, uh, Lu...
- I mean, I'm starting to wonder

04:33.760 --> 04:35.946
if the detective has some
sort of biological dysfunction.

04:35.981 --> 04:37.565
- Lucifer.
- 'Cause, I mean, I appeal

04:37.600 --> 04:38.941
to the feral urge in all women.

04:38.976 --> 04:41.688
Certainly, well, certainly you
can attest to that, can't you?

04:41.723 --> 04:43.155
Uh, Lucifer, stop.

04:43.190 --> 04:44.744
Yes, of course, sorry. Payment first.

04:44.779 --> 04:47.505
Uh, no. No, no, no, no, no, no. No! No!

04:47.540 --> 04:48.745
Hmm?

04:48.780 --> 04:52.281
Lucifer, this is George.

04:53.318 --> 04:54.894
George, Lucifer.

04:55.048 --> 04:56.981
Lucifer, George.

04:57.050 --> 04:59.684
(chuckles softly)

04:59.719 --> 05:01.385
Oops.

05:10.363 --> 05:12.630
- Dan, if you're here to scold me...
- No.

05:12.806 --> 05:15.422
I just got off the phone
with the lieutenant.

05:15.534 --> 05:17.134
There's a case.

05:18.479 --> 05:19.845
Day four.

05:19.913 --> 05:22.813
Down to three meat sticks,
a half a bottle of water,

05:22.951 --> 05:25.551
217 miles to L.A.

05:25.641 --> 05:27.541
I'm not sure we're gonna make it,

05:27.647 --> 05:31.030
'cause my brother drives
like a narcoleptic old lady.

05:31.093 --> 05:33.117
Say hi, Grandma!

05:33.153 --> 05:34.627
(laughs)

05:34.662 --> 05:36.883
No, that's our only nourishment!

05:36.918 --> 05:38.914
DAN: Her name's Lindsay Jolson.

05:38.964 --> 05:40.405
Just turned 22.

05:40.507 --> 05:42.818
She went missing catering
a Players' Club event.

05:42.904 --> 05:43.957
Players' Club?

05:43.992 --> 05:45.824
It's one of those skeezy
pickup artist groups.

05:45.859 --> 05:48.166
You know, that teach
geeks how to be sex gods.

05:48.314 --> 05:49.095
Got it.

05:49.130 --> 05:51.969
Lindsay was last seen
talking to the lead scumbag.

05:53.664 --> 05:56.073
The founder, Carver Cruz.

05:56.689 --> 05:57.926
So he was interrogated?

05:57.961 --> 06:00.232
Yep, but his lawyer did all the talking.

06:00.267 --> 06:01.752
And with no proof, we're stuck.

06:01.787 --> 06:04.248
But there's a Players'
seminar and after-party today.

06:04.284 --> 06:05.938
And you need to go undercover.

06:05.973 --> 06:07.557
Why me? I'm homicide.

06:07.592 --> 06:08.975
Because you're our best way in.

06:09.010 --> 06:10.196
- I am?
- Apparently these events

06:10.231 --> 06:12.219
are pretty exclusive, and
when I saw the guest list,

06:12.254 --> 06:14.157
I recognized one of the names.

06:14.298 --> 06:17.698
I guess a lot of high-end
club owners are invited.

06:17.893 --> 06:19.426
Oh, come on.

06:19.504 --> 06:21.032
No. You're kidding.

06:21.067 --> 06:22.764
(chuckles) I wish I was.

06:22.799 --> 06:24.777
- Lucifer's on the list?
- Yeah.

06:24.812 --> 06:26.608
Yeah, of course he is.

06:26.643 --> 06:28.161
(sighs)

06:28.258 --> 06:30.483
Look...

06:30.587 --> 06:33.669
the last thing I want is the guy I found

06:33.704 --> 06:35.592
making my half-naked wife
breakfast this morning

06:35.627 --> 06:37.082
spending more time with her,

06:37.117 --> 06:38.883
separated or not.

06:39.482 --> 06:40.284
But...

06:40.320 --> 06:42.296
This is the best option.

06:42.370 --> 06:45.113
I wouldn't ask, but I just keep thinking,

06:45.685 --> 06:48.158
what if this was our daughter?

06:51.274 --> 06:54.595
The detective seems
like a very lovely woman.

06:54.630 --> 06:56.351
Well, I suppose, but still, she's human.

06:56.386 --> 06:58.803
Why is she able to refuse my charms?

06:58.838 --> 07:00.543
I mean, is this thing on?

07:00.578 --> 07:03.012
Yes, yes.

07:03.288 --> 07:05.855
Definitely on.

07:07.146 --> 07:08.033
(sighs)

07:08.087 --> 07:11.518
It's not that you're afraid that
you don't have power over Chloe.

07:11.607 --> 07:14.187
It's that you're afraid
that she has power over you,

07:14.222 --> 07:15.800
but neither one is true.

07:15.835 --> 07:17.221
- No?
- No.

07:17.369 --> 07:20.258
People don't have power over us.

07:20.293 --> 07:22.326
We give it to them.

07:22.362 --> 07:24.723
You have to take your power back.

07:24.963 --> 07:26.046
Right, go on.

07:26.130 --> 07:30.670
You say she's nothing special, but
I think you've put her on a pedestal.

07:30.779 --> 07:33.004
You need to really get to know her,

07:33.039 --> 07:35.341
warts and all. (chuckles)

07:35.376 --> 07:37.331
I'm sure she has some.

07:37.366 --> 07:38.772
(chuckles)

07:38.807 --> 07:42.788
So, (clears throat) demystify her

07:42.905 --> 07:45.766
by bringing her back
down to your own level.

07:48.278 --> 07:49.777
You're right.

07:49.850 --> 07:51.591
It's not her, it's me.

07:51.653 --> 07:53.683
I need to take back control.

07:53.718 --> 07:55.723
I need to behave like I always have.

07:55.779 --> 07:57.649
Good. So you understand.

07:57.713 --> 07:58.545
Yes.

07:58.589 --> 07:59.718
Yes. (chuckles)

07:59.753 --> 08:02.520
I mean, it seems obvious now, actually.

08:02.555 --> 08:04.415
I need to have sex with her.

08:04.477 --> 08:07.249
Uh... no, uh, that's not what I said.

08:07.310 --> 08:10.847
No, no, no, you're a genius. I mean,
that's the best way to lose interest, right?

08:10.933 --> 08:12.668
Right. Good-o.

08:13.125 --> 08:14.044
Hmm.

08:14.079 --> 08:14.772
Thanks, love.

08:14.807 --> 08:16.455
Oh, sure.

08:16.670 --> 08:18.973
- Payment next time, okay?
- Uh...

08:19.617 --> 08:21.250
Um...

08:28.874 --> 08:30.561
CHLOE: Her name's Lindsay Jolson.

08:30.596 --> 08:31.295
Mm-hmm.

08:31.330 --> 08:33.994
She's been missing almost three full days.

08:34.272 --> 08:36.162
Right, so just ask me one more time.

08:36.240 --> 08:37.886
Lucifer, there's a girl missing.

08:37.922 --> 08:39.695
(chuckles) Yes, it's just not every day

08:39.730 --> 08:43.282
someone kicks you out of your house,
then three hours later asks you on a date.

08:43.335 --> 08:45.666
It's not a date. It's a work thing.

08:45.743 --> 08:48.235
- Oh.
- And are you gonna help me or not?

08:48.868 --> 08:49.975
All right.

08:50.116 --> 08:53.351
But only 'cause it coincides
perfectly with my own plan.

08:53.898 --> 08:55.019
And what plan is that?

08:55.054 --> 08:57.321
Well, to have sex with you, of course.

08:57.669 --> 08:59.079
(laughs) Okay.

08:59.114 --> 09:01.766
Wait, you and I... well,
there is no you and I.

09:01.801 --> 09:03.473
There's a professional situation,

09:03.508 --> 09:05.496
- and I just need you...
- See, you need me.

09:05.531 --> 09:07.445
The department needs you,
because you're the one...

09:07.480 --> 09:08.799
I'm the one?

09:09.679 --> 09:11.717
On the list for the Player thing.

09:11.752 --> 09:13.738
You're quite adorable
when you're flustered.

09:13.773 --> 09:16.368
I... I'm not flustered.

09:16.403 --> 09:17.199
I'm nauseous.

09:17.281 --> 09:19.544
Now you're blushing; I'd
say I'm making headway.

09:19.610 --> 09:24.428
Okay, look, let me make
myself perfectly clear.

09:24.577 --> 09:26.217
I will never,

09:26.252 --> 09:29.420
ever, ever sleep with you.

09:29.503 --> 09:30.821
Never.

09:30.857 --> 09:32.323
Okay? Got it?

09:32.358 --> 09:34.158
Playing hard to get, I like it.

09:34.193 --> 09:36.727
When Hell freezes over, Lucifer.

09:36.763 --> 09:38.329
I can arrange that, actually.

09:38.418 --> 09:40.368
Get in the car.

09:41.567 --> 09:43.801
♪ ♪

09:43.835 --> 09:47.411
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

09:51.535 --> 09:55.550
