She's not even from L.A.

12:01.331 --> 12:03.595
I'm all she has out here.

12:03.983 --> 12:05.481
She's all I have.

12:05.559 --> 12:06.650
Kevin, I promise you,

12:06.685 --> 12:09.325
if anyone here hurt your
sister, I'll find them.

12:09.360 --> 12:10.650
LUCIFER: And I'll punish them.

12:10.685 --> 12:12.300
Any method you prefer.

12:12.335 --> 12:15.130
Nice solid flogging. Get the ol'
swamp nuts in a vice, you know.

12:15.165 --> 12:16.713
Okay. It's time to go now.

12:16.748 --> 12:19.939
Let us handle this, and if we
hear anything, we'll be in touch.

12:20.006 --> 12:21.355
Okay. Thank you.

12:21.452 --> 12:22.269
Yeah.

12:22.330 --> 12:23.873
We've got this.

12:25.366 --> 12:27.162
You have to admit, we're quite a good team.

12:27.208 --> 12:31.290
If you weren't so pent-up sexually,
we'd be firing on all cylinders, I'd say.

12:37.597 --> 12:40.391
I'm assuming you learned most of
your moves at events like these.

12:40.443 --> 12:42.291
I've never been to something
like this before in my life.

12:42.326 --> 12:44.591
I certainly don't need any
help getting women into bed.

12:44.626 --> 12:45.625
Till...

12:45.672 --> 12:47.705
Were you hit on the
head when you were small?

12:47.950 --> 12:50.050
(sighs)

12:51.060 --> 12:53.193
No?

12:54.968 --> 12:57.101
("Eye of the Tiger" by Survivor playing)

13:02.742 --> 13:05.776
(crowd cheering)

13:18.589 --> 13:23.103
We are biological machines.

13:23.184 --> 13:26.655
We... are warriors.

13:26.690 --> 13:30.654
We... are players!

13:30.689 --> 13:32.789
(crowd cheering)

13:35.083 --> 13:38.567
Gentlemen, we are animals.

13:38.657 --> 13:42.892
Men are the wolves, and women...

13:44.169 --> 13:45.969
...are the fluffy bunnies.

13:46.004 --> 13:47.692
(laughter)

13:47.727 --> 13:51.107
So we must prepare ourselves for the hunt.

13:51.143 --> 13:51.919
How?

13:51.954 --> 13:53.870
ALL: "Follow the list."

13:53.905 --> 13:56.080
Yes! The C.K.C.

13:56.162 --> 13:58.807
The Conduct of Kick-ass Cavemen.

13:58.885 --> 14:01.885
One: Be seen.

14:01.931 --> 14:03.197
People pay for this?

14:03.232 --> 14:04.665
Yeah, 5,000 bucks.

14:04.700 --> 14:06.113
CARVER: Stand out.

14:06.173 --> 14:09.072
The peacock, the lion with his mane.

14:09.211 --> 14:13.113
Two: Be a protector.

14:13.165 --> 14:13.844
Duh.

14:13.914 --> 14:16.995
Women are hardwired to hook up with someone

14:17.110 --> 14:18.722
who can help them survive.

14:18.817 --> 14:21.471
It is simple biology, man.

14:21.506 --> 14:24.409
Three: Be brave.

14:24.464 --> 14:25.470
Take risks.

14:25.517 --> 14:27.076
Oh, maybe you should take notes.

14:27.112 --> 14:30.493
CARVER: Four: Be a leader of men.

14:30.557 --> 14:32.831
And the most elusive.

14:32.895 --> 14:37.478
Five: Be confident.

14:37.619 --> 14:39.849
You... are...

14:39.918 --> 14:41.691
a player!

14:41.726 --> 14:42.659
Own it!

14:42.694 --> 14:43.635
(crowd cheering)

14:43.706 --> 14:46.437
Excuse-excuse me! Excuse me, question!

14:46.569 --> 14:47.400
CHLOE: What are you doing?

14:47.435 --> 14:48.991
CARVER: The Q&A's after the speech, buddy.

14:49.026 --> 14:50.667
LUCIFER: No, but it's quite pressing.

14:50.702 --> 14:54.852
What if you have all those manly whatnots
and a woman still doesn't respond?

14:54.887 --> 14:58.054
You may think you have them, but you don't.

14:58.089 --> 14:59.594
- Yeah.
- That's why you're here, right?

14:59.629 --> 15:01.878
So, gentlemen, you follow these rules,

15:01.957 --> 15:05.574
and you will bed any Betty
you desire, guaranteed.

15:05.609 --> 15:08.818
LUCIFER: No. No. No, no, no. I'm certain
I've got everything on your little list,

15:08.853 --> 15:10.587
and more, actually,

15:10.622 --> 15:14.347
yet this woman here won't have sex with me.

15:14.480 --> 15:16.350
(laughter)

15:16.453 --> 15:18.661
Just listen to the speech, buddy.

15:18.737 --> 15:20.180
The system works.

15:20.244 --> 15:21.919
No, but I doubt that.

15:21.974 --> 15:24.411
Because... because if
I can't "bed a Betty,"

15:24.446 --> 15:26.179
then how do you possibly expect

15:26.214 --> 15:29.111
any of these poor miscreants to succeed?

15:29.146 --> 15:30.193
(crowd grumbles)

15:30.228 --> 15:33.792
Especially when they're taking
advice from a-a wanker such as you?

15:33.827 --> 15:35.178
All right, just sit down, man.

15:35.213 --> 15:36.538
Yeah, Lucifer, sit down.

15:36.638 --> 15:39.182
I-I just... could we get
the spotlight over here?

15:39.217 --> 15:40.352
(chuckles) Do we have that?

15:40.387 --> 15:42.785
Yeah, yeah. But on-on her.

15:42.902 --> 15:44.425
Good. Right.

15:44.460 --> 15:45.821
Now, you're the expert.

15:45.892 --> 15:47.458
You tell me what's wrong with this picture.

15:47.493 --> 15:49.512
I mean, I'm me.

15:49.547 --> 15:50.154
Right?

15:50.189 --> 15:51.461
And she...

15:51.496 --> 15:53.363
Well, she's a cop, for starters.

15:53.398 --> 15:54.197
(crowd grumbles)

15:54.232 --> 15:55.898
She's a cop?

15:55.934 --> 15:58.188
Yes. I mean, talk about the
shallow end of the dating pool.

15:58.233 --> 15:59.623
This is private property.

15:59.658 --> 16:02.379
Unless you have a warrant, you
need to leave here immediately.

16:02.414 --> 16:03.473
Security!

16:03.508 --> 16:04.808
Security, her, out.

16:04.843 --> 16:06.736
Okay, we're gonna take a
ten-minute intermission.

16:06.771 --> 16:09.711
- All right? Thank you.
- I haven't finished.

16:09.900 --> 16:11.301
All right.

16:11.435 --> 16:13.435
Oh, it's you again.

16:15.382 --> 16:17.816
Have you two...?

16:20.174 --> 16:22.291
I know. I'm-I'm sorry, Lieutenant.

16:22.326 --> 16:23.934
I... No. No.

16:23.969 --> 16:25.628
I've got it under control.

16:25.664 --> 16:27.166
And Mr. Morningstar, too, yes.

16:27.201 --> 16:28.499
Let me talk to him.

16:28.534 --> 16:29.667
It's a her, and no.

16:29.702 --> 16:31.100
Really? Your boss is a she?

16:31.161 --> 16:32.689
Even better. Give me
the phone, I'll fix it.

16:32.724 --> 16:33.910
No, you can't fix this!

16:33.945 --> 16:35.438
You've already said enough.

16:35.542 --> 16:36.220
Sorry!

16:36.292 --> 16:38.092
Not you.

16:38.221 --> 16:41.048
Yes, I-I'll figure out
a way into the party.

16:41.083 --> 16:42.157
It's not a problem.

16:42.192 --> 16:44.883
And-and again, I...

16:45.117 --> 16:48.615
So we're going to the Player after-party.

16:48.717 --> 16:49.690
Not you. I am.

16:49.725 --> 16:52.169
Well, I'm not sure how that's possible,
now that you've blown your cover.

16:52.204 --> 16:53.733
Well, that was 100% your fault.

16:53.768 --> 16:55.191
I beg to differ.

16:55.226 --> 16:57.809
None of that would have happened if
you'd just complied with my request.

16:57.844 --> 17:00.822
Do you honestly think you can just ask
people to have sex with you and they will?

17:00.857 --> 17:02.532
Well, I usually don't
have to ask, actually.

17:02.567 --> 17:04.304
But trust me, it'd be a win-win.

17:04.339 --> 17:05.460
And probably another win after that.

17:05.494 --> 17:07.672
I mean, I have tremendous stamina.

17:07.707 --> 17:09.489
There's a girl missing, Lucifer.

17:09.523 --> 17:11.324
She's probably in some hellhole somewhere,

17:11.358 --> 17:13.483
scared out of her mind,
if she's even still alive.

17:13.519 --> 17:16.266
And I found out the party
is a cash-only event.

17:16.300 --> 17:17.605
That's a first for Carver.

17:17.640 --> 17:20.967
So our only suspect's probably
about to run off to Mexico,

17:21.006 --> 17:23.118
and you're worried about boning me?

17:23.154 --> 17:24.681
You're right. Sorry.

17:24.760 --> 17:25.954
- Let's find the girl. Okay?
- Yes.

17:25.990 --> 17:27.694
Sex later.

17:27.839 --> 17:28.992
Kidding.

17:29.067 --> 17:29.992
Sort of.

17:30.028 --> 17:30.687
(sighs)

17:30.722 --> 17:32.295
So where's the party?

17:32.330 --> 17:33.486
Cold Bar.

17:33.521 --> 17:34.597
Really?

17:34.632 --> 17:37.033
Well, that place is
notoriously overpriced to rent.

17:37.068 --> 17:39.768
If Carver wants cash, he
shouldn't have it there.

17:41.330 --> 17:43.430
No, he shouldn't.

17:45.598 --> 17:48.004
I think I just figured
out how you can fix this.

17:48.044 --> 17:49.103
Oh?

17:49.180 --> 17:50.883
Do tell.

18:01.427 --> 18:03.861
(wings whooshing)

18:10.829 --> 18:12.565
Miss me?

18:20.271 --> 18:23.643
I know why you're here. I
won't help you, Amenadiel.

18:23.715 --> 18:25.205
One way or another, Maze,

18:25.240 --> 18:28.135
I am gonna change your mind, so...

18:28.170 --> 18:31.259
You're gonna help me
get Lucifer back to Hell.

18:31.368 --> 18:33.752
Don't make it painful.

18:33.787 --> 18:34.919
(laughs)

18:34.955 --> 18:36.847
You forget.

18:36.882 --> 18:38.089
I love pain.

18:38.125 --> 18:39.924
♪ ♪

18:39.960 --> 18:41.793
(grunting)

18:45.098 --> 18:46.626
I'm an angel.

18:46.697 --> 18:49.063
You can't beat me, little demon.

18:51.151 --> 18:53.489
Stop and hear me out.

18:53.755 --> 18:55.254
(chuckles)

18:57.044 --> 18:58.777
Men...

18:59.346 --> 19:01.146
...they always want to talk.

19:01.181 --> 19:03.214
♪ ♪

19:16.496 --> 19:17.629
(grunts)

19:17.664 --> 19:19.270
Enough!

19:19.348 --> 19:21.915
We want the same thing!

19:22.068 --> 19:24.068
Oh, do we?

19:24.104 --> 19:25.737
Let's see.

19:30.938 --> 19:32.872
Uh-oh.

19:33.338 --> 19:36.105
Did I hit a nerve?

19:38.452 --> 19:40.618
Mazikeen, we both know

19:40.654 --> 19:44.051
that something has
fundamentally changed in Lucifer.

19:44.086 --> 19:45.690
Now, aren't you even
the least bit concerned?

19:45.771 --> 19:46.875
No.

19:46.910 --> 19:48.869
It's a phase. It'll pass.

19:48.904 --> 19:50.395
You're lying to me.

19:50.430 --> 19:53.064
You're lying to yourself.

19:55.584 --> 19:57.150
Now, we can help each other.

19:57.185 --> 19:59.408
We can get him back to where he belongs,

19:59.443 --> 20:03.112
if you could just provide
me with a weak spot.

20:03.443 --> 20:05.081
Some insight.

20:05.253 --> 20:06.824
No...

20:06.873 --> 20:09.006
means no.

20:15.129 --> 20:17.362
♪ ♪

20:27.784 --> 20:30.351
Uh... hello?

20:30.504 --> 20:32.120
Uh, Lucifer?

20:32.213 --> 20:34.832
LUCIFER: Be out in a
moment. Just getting ready.

20:34.917 --> 20:36.268
Okay.

20:36.347 --> 20:38.280
Uh, did you do what I told you to do

20:38.315 --> 20:40.332
and call Carver about the Player's Club?

20:40.405 --> 20:42.572
LUCIFER: Make yourself a drink, Detective.

20:42.695 --> 20:45.824
No. No. No more drinks.

20:45.944 --> 20:47.346
No more blurred lines.

20:47.381 --> 20:51.116
No more breaking into my house
or trying to sleep with me.

20:51.291 --> 20:54.032
Look, this is a professional relationship.

20:54.138 --> 20:57.031
I'm a police officer, and you...

20:57.114 --> 20:59.347
(gasps)

21:02.077 --> 21:03.301
(laughs)

21:03.467 --> 21:05.335
...are naked. Oh...

21:05.370 --> 21:09.138
Speaking of my surprise visit yesterday,
I decided turnabout's fair play.

21:09.173 --> 21:12.049
You know, tit for tat
sort of thing. (chuckles)

21:12.084 --> 21:14.445
This is beyond inappropriate.

21:14.512 --> 21:15.947
And brave, wouldn't you say?

21:15.982 --> 21:19.484
Number three on the
C.K.C. list: take risks.

21:20.433 --> 21:21.532
(clears throat)

21:27.250 --> 21:28.654
Okay. Just...

21:28.689 --> 21:31.103
Lucifer, put some freakin' clothes on.

21:31.610 --> 21:33.182
All right.

21:33.241 --> 21:36.245
But seriously, darling, are you well?

21:36.970 --> 21:39.781
The berries are ripe and
ready to be harvested.

21:39.867 --> 21:42.137
I mean, look at me.

21:42.172 --> 21:43.838
Huh?

21:50.300 --> 21:53.868
Now, you can't argue with that, can you?

21:57.319 --> 22:00.258
What happened to...

22:00.387 --> 22:01.880
My God.

22:01.974 --> 22:02.827
Oh, oh.

22:02.862 --> 22:04.562
Well, yes, I suppose it is his fault.

22:04.598 --> 22:05.630
Whose fault?

22:05.665 --> 22:06.926
My father.

22:07.004 --> 22:08.366
Your dad did that to you?

22:08.401 --> 22:11.092
No, no, no. That's
where I cut my wings off.

22:11.127 --> 22:12.804
- (sighs) What?
- Well, I didn't.

22:12.839 --> 22:14.361
Maze did. I told her to.

22:14.396 --> 22:15.941
N-No.

22:15.976 --> 22:17.964
Seriously.

22:18.050 --> 22:19.646
What is that?

22:23.346 --> 22:25.513
Don't, please.

22:30.490 --> 22:32.423
Okay.

22:32.459 --> 22:36.227
I should get dressed.
Otherwise, we'll miss the party.

22:36.262 --> 22:38.084
So you did make the call?

22:38.119 --> 22:39.540
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

22:39.575 --> 22:40.598
Party's at Lux.

22:40.633 --> 22:43.029
Turns out, the words "open
bar" are indeed effective.

22:43.064 --> 22:45.263
So good on you.

22:45.298 --> 22:46.052
Okay.

22:46.087 --> 22:48.487
Can't go wearing that scruffy little getup.

22:48.522 --> 22:50.722
You'll stick out like a sore cop.

22:52.137 --> 22:54.571
♪ ♪

23:00.612 --> 23:02.507
Where did you get this dress anyhow?

23:02.542 --> 23:04.922
Oh, it was left behind by
one of my overnight guests.

23:05.005 --> 23:06.624
What was she wearing when she left?

23:06.660 --> 23:08.126
- A smile.
- Mm.

23:08.161 --> 23:11.205
If I get an STD from this
thing, I'm gonna kill you.

23:11.260 --> 23:13.331
Oh, there he is.

23:13.366 --> 23:16.447
CHLOE: Oh, he doesn't
look suspicious at all.

23:16.482 --> 23:18.670
Hmm, so what's the plan, Detective?

23:18.705 --> 23:20.487
Avoid him for now.

23:20.522 --> 23:22.913
Mingle, find people who
were at the party last week.

23:22.948 --> 23:25.376
See if anyone saw Carver
with our missing girl.

23:25.412 --> 23:26.598
- Hey.
- Hi.

23:26.633 --> 23:29.166
- Are you from Tennessee?
- No.

23:29.201 --> 23:31.115
Because you're the only ten I see.

23:31.151 --> 23:33.799
LUCIFER: Oh, you poor soul.
Does that actually work?

23:33.877 --> 23:35.653
- No.
- No, I didn't think so.

23:35.689 --> 23:36.960
(laughs) It's cute.

23:36.995 --> 23:38.189
It-it is?

23:38.224 --> 23:39.478
Yeah.

23:39.513 --> 23:41.426
Y-You're cute.

23:41.461 --> 23:42.627
You're really cute.

23:42.662 --> 23:45.329
Hey, were you at that party last week?

23:45.365 --> 23:46.980
Uh, no, actually, this is my first.

23:47.015 --> 23:48.800
Okay.

23:49.591 --> 23:51.258
MAN: I love this song!

23:51.293 --> 23:52.370
Okay.

23:52.405 --> 23:54.516
Hey, oh, were you at the party last week?

23:54.551 --> 23:57.769
Uh, I think the dress may
have backfired, actually.

23:59.045 --> 24:01.659
I think we've been spotted.

24:02.818 --> 24:05.164
Clearly a man with nothing to hide.

24:06.186 --> 24:07.818
Move!

24:07.853 --> 24:09.420
- Get out of the way!
- (people screaming)

24:09.456 --> 24:10.888
Just...

24:10.924 --> 24:11.989
get out.

24:12.025 --> 24:13.491
Move!

24:13.526 --> 24:15.906
Just come...

24:16.132 --> 24:17.578
Give me the gun, Carver.

24:17.613 --> 24:18.830
Just-just let me go, okay?

24:18.935 --> 24:19.924
I need to go!

24:19.959 --> 24:23.387
I'm afraid that's not possible, but
I do have another option for you.

24:23.422 --> 24:24.902
How about a broken back, hmm?

24:25.405 --> 24:26.871
(groans)

24:27.874 --> 24:29.945
You don't understand, I have to go!

24:29.980 --> 24:31.560
They're gonna kill her now!

24:31.595 --> 24:33.144
You just killed Lindsay!

24:33.210 --> 24:34.985
They? They who?

24:35.715 --> 24:37.790
The people who took her.

24:46.360 --> 24:49.163
- Where is Lindsay?
- I don't know, okay?

24:49.198 --> 24:51.974
I swear to you, somebody kidnapped her.

24:52.083 --> 24:54.098
If that's the case, then why
wouldn't you go to the cops?

24:54.133 --> 24:56.572
Because they said they'd kill her if I did.

24:56.608 --> 24:57.640
Maybe they already have.

24:57.675 --> 24:58.856
Excuse me, dear, I don't know why we bother

24:58.891 --> 25:01.332
with all these pithy
little police questions.

25:01.367 --> 25:02.945
Tell me...

25:04.047 --> 25:05.798
...what game's the player playing, eh?

25:05.880 --> 25:07.826
What are you after?

25:10.101 --> 25:12.229
I just want Lindsay back.

25:12.397 --> 25:15.146
I swear, I would never hurt her.

25:15.974 --> 25:18.261
I love her.

25:19.148 --> 25:21.605
But she's a fluffy bunny.

25:21.640 --> 25:22.384
You're a wolf.

25:22.419 --> 25:24.862
You-You've built an empire on
the objectification of women.

25:24.897 --> 25:26.892
Yeah, I know. I'm a complete hypocrite.

25:26.958 --> 25:30.092
But I-I would give
anything to get her back.

25:30.208 --> 25:31.652
You humans.

25:31.687 --> 25:34.204
(chuckles): You never cease to amaze.

25:34.239 --> 25:36.986
Okay, Carver,

25:37.021 --> 25:38.214
say what you're saying is true.

25:38.249 --> 25:39.916
How long have you and
Lindsay been together?

25:39.951 --> 25:41.284
Four months.

25:41.319 --> 25:42.874
Next Tuesday.

25:42.952 --> 25:44.625
I tried to keep it quiet,

25:44.730 --> 25:48.303
'cause, you know, I'm
the man and everything.

25:48.412 --> 25:49.678
I guess it got out.

25:49.713 --> 25:53.335
So you're saying you slept with
Lindsay on multiple occasions,

25:53.370 --> 25:54.931
but you still want to be with her?

25:55.020 --> 25:57.592
Yes, and for the rest of my life.

25:57.627 --> 25:58.448
Well, after four months,

25:58.483 --> 26:01.593
you haven't got her, you know,
out of your system? (chuckles)

26:01.628 --> 26:03.125
How's that possible?

26:03.345 --> 26:04.711
CHLOE: Okay.

26:06.110 --> 26:08.044
You have no idea where
they're holding Lindsay?

26:08.079 --> 26:12.009
No. But they did send this to me...

26:12.461 --> 26:14.128
...after the seminar.

26:16.928 --> 26:19.121
Said no more cops or she's dead.

26:19.201 --> 26:22.391
So the kidnappers were
there yesterday watching you.

26:22.868 --> 26:24.567
CARVER: I just hope they
weren't at the party.

26:24.629 --> 26:25.838
If they hurt her, I...

26:25.873 --> 26:27.568
CHLOE: It's okay.

26:27.982 --> 26:31.267
Is there anyone you suspect
that might do this to you?

26:31.302 --> 26:31.977
Enemies?

26:32.012 --> 26:34.709
Uh, I'm kind of a polarizing guy.

26:34.841 --> 26:36.511
Okay, the hater list is long.

26:36.546 --> 26:39.529
Hello there, this is Lucifer Morningstar.

26:42.469 --> 26:43.583
Who are you talking to?

26:43.618 --> 26:45.485
- Shh.
- Do not shush me.

26:45.520 --> 26:47.624
- Who's on the phone?
- All one word, that's right.

26:47.659 --> 26:50.757
Yes, I'll be speaking on
Carver's behalf from now on.

26:50.792 --> 26:53.056
(chuckles) No, I'm not a cop.

26:53.091 --> 26:54.264
I assure you.

26:54.299 --> 26:56.259
- Is that the...
- Yes, it's the kidnappers.

26:56.294 --> 26:57.574
What are you doing?

26:57.609 --> 26:59.370
Of course we have the money.

26:59.405 --> 27:01.097
Just give me a time and location.

27:01.132 --> 27:02.591
- (tutting)
- Give me the phone.

27:02.626 --> 27:04.310
No, I promise you, no police.

27:04.345 --> 27:05.773
All right?

27:05.820 --> 27:06.822
Okay, then.

27:06.867 --> 27:07.993
- See you shortly. Bye-bye.
- Wait, wait.

27:08.028 --> 27:09.538
Wait, we need proof of life.

27:09.574 --> 27:11.173
Oh.

27:11.209 --> 27:12.808
Um, just a minute.

27:12.875 --> 27:14.970
How do we know Lindsay's still alive?

27:15.100 --> 27:16.599
No, they've hung up.

27:17.431 --> 27:18.597
What are you doing?

27:18.649 --> 27:20.215
Not to worry. I've handled it.

27:20.250 --> 27:22.465
I'll be making an exchange
on your behalf this evening.

27:22.509 --> 27:24.714
Cash for your lady love, all right?

27:24.800 --> 27:26.191
Really?

27:26.246 --> 27:29.283
Uh, but why would you do that for me?

27:29.338 --> 27:31.898
Well, (chuckles) isn't it obvious?

27:31.960 --> 27:34.053
Number two on your list: be a protector.

27:34.088 --> 27:35.341
Is it working?

27:35.376 --> 27:36.841
You're not doing this alone.

27:36.876 --> 27:37.957
Afraid so.

27:37.992 --> 27:39.235
I promised, no police.

27:39.270 --> 27:41.999
A deal's a deal, especially
one with the Devil. (chuckles)

27:42.120 --> 27:45.111
Besides, I'm the only one
not risking his life on this.

27:45.146 --> 27:47.480
Immortal, remember?

27:49.318 --> 27:51.351
(phone chimes)

27:52.084 --> 27:53.603
LINDSAY (crying): Carver,

27:53.718 --> 27:55.418
I'm all right.

27:56.518 --> 27:57.910
I'm a...

27:57.992 --> 28:00.376
I don't know where I am.

28:00.501 --> 28:02.625
Please come get me.

28:03.020 --> 28:04.236
I love you.

28:04.271 --> 28:06.751
Please. (sobbing)

28:08.166 --> 28:09.259
I'm coming with you.

28:09.294 --> 28:10.821
No, I can't let you do that.

28:10.856 --> 28:12.799
I'm not gonna call this in,
but you have to stay here.

28:12.834 --> 28:15.268
No discussion. I'm coming with you.

28:15.338 --> 28:16.372
Fine.

28:16.411 --> 28:18.674
You'll have to wait in the car.

28:18.709 --> 28:21.744
♪ ♪

28:44.480 --> 28:45.660
Ten more minutes.

28:45.695 --> 28:46.969
Patience.

28:47.090 --> 28:48.499
Something doesn't feel right.

28:48.596 --> 28:51.326
Well, of course it
doesn't. It's a kidnapping.

28:52.777 --> 28:54.944
Cool ranch puff?

28:54.979 --> 28:55.878
No, thanks.

28:55.913 --> 28:57.806
- No?
- Mm.

28:57.877 --> 28:59.557
It's funny, isn't it? You'd
think the king of hellfire

28:59.592 --> 29:03.619
would be more of a flaming hot
guy, but love these bad boys.

29:03.654 --> 29:07.370
Okay, let's say you really are the Devil.

29:07.487 --> 29:09.511
All-powerful, immortal, blah, blah, blah.

29:09.586 --> 29:11.429
Does that mean you don't feel pain at all?

29:11.464 --> 29:13.369
Hmm. I like this line of questioning.

29:13.404 --> 29:15.431
Does this mean you're
finally coming around?

29:15.466 --> 29:18.067
No. Just answer the question.

29:18.102 --> 29:21.146
(chuckles) Well, I... I do feel something,

29:21.181 --> 29:23.666
but it's not pain so much as, uh,

29:23.701 --> 29:25.565
a pressure, a nuisance, really.

29:25.600 --> 29:28.972
Okay, so what does it
feel like if you get shot?

29:32.350 --> 29:33.177
Ow.

29:33.234 --> 29:34.800
Well, you asked.

29:34.952 --> 29:37.057
But that's it? Like, a
bullet just bounces off you?

29:37.092 --> 29:40.461
Well, there's no wound or
blood, if that's what you mean.

29:40.496 --> 29:42.714
Can verify with something
sharp if you like.

29:42.749 --> 29:45.294
No, it's not necessary.
It's tempting though.

29:45.329 --> 29:46.595
Huh.

29:46.631 --> 29:49.566
So, does this mean that you believe me?

29:49.683 --> 29:52.911
I'm afraid I can't offer anything
obvious like a tail as proof.

29:52.946 --> 29:55.089
- And so no horns.
- No, afraid not.

29:55.124 --> 29:56.906
That's the stuff of movies and TV.

29:56.941 --> 29:57.607
Mm-hmm.

29:57.642 --> 29:59.041
They always get it wrong.

29:59.076 --> 30:00.917
Well, look, I-I (laughs) have to admit,

30:00.952 --> 30:02.727
I've seen some things I can't explain,

30:02.762 --> 30:05.729
but I don't believe in
all that Bible stuff.

30:05.795 --> 30:07.906
So you're an atheist. How ironic.

30:07.975 --> 30:09.824
No, not exactly.

30:09.918 --> 30:13.722
I do believe there's good
and evil and right and wrong.

30:13.758 --> 30:17.149
But the whole fiery damnation thing, no.

30:17.214 --> 30:18.247
Does it scare you?

30:18.329 --> 30:22.755
No, I mean, how could I be scared
of something that I don't believe in?

30:25.269 --> 30:27.559
Do I scare you?

30:30.274 --> 30:31.674
No.

30:36.436 --> 30:37.716
Is that Carver?

30:37.779 --> 30:39.078
Hmm?

30:40.334 --> 30:42.254
How did he get here?

30:42.328 --> 30:43.325
Oh, he must have followed us.

30:43.360 --> 30:45.396
- Well done, Detective.
- CHLOE: No, he didn't follow us.

30:45.466 --> 30:47.045
He must have gotten the address somehow.

30:47.080 --> 30:48.578
Or someone told him.

30:48.613 --> 30:52.013
Either way, he's gonna get
someone killed, probably himself.

30:53.090 --> 30:56.114
This love thing makes you
all quite stupid, doesn't it?

31:10.047 --> 31:12.181
(whispers): Lucifer!

31:16.520 --> 31:18.654
(whispers): Lucifer!

31:22.994 --> 31:23.854
(lock clicks)

31:23.889 --> 31:26.905
Sorry, but I gave my word... no police.

31:26.976 --> 31:28.054
Seriously?

31:28.117 --> 31:29.341
Don't worry, Detective.

31:29.376 --> 31:30.899
I'm immortal, remember?

31:30.986 --> 31:33.639
- I knew it.
- (line ringing)

31:33.733 --> 31:35.653
Hey, guys, I'm gonna need
you sooner than I thought.

31:35.688 --> 31:36.897
Is SWAT ready?

31:47.330 --> 31:49.564
♪ ♪

32:02.045 --> 32:03.010
(screams)

32:03.046 --> 32:03.848
(chuckles)

32:03.883 --> 32:04.941
Manly as ever.

32:04.976 --> 32:06.237
Why are you here?

32:06.272 --> 32:07.713
We had a perfectly good plan in place.

32:07.748 --> 32:10.219
Well, after you left, the
kidnappers called back.

32:10.254 --> 32:14.216
They said they changed their
minds, and I come or the deal's off.

32:14.281 --> 32:16.748
Oh, that sounds sinister.

32:17.474 --> 32:19.594
Just hand over the cash,

32:19.707 --> 32:21.078
and no one gets hurt.

32:21.113 --> 32:23.046
Yes, right. Got it here.

32:23.140 --> 32:25.474
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait! Where's Lindsay?!

32:25.547 --> 32:26.565
I want to see her.

32:26.600 --> 32:29.136
No. My rules.

32:29.172 --> 32:30.089
Money first.

32:30.134 --> 32:33.008
Now, Mr. Kidnapper, I believe
that's a fair request actually,

32:33.079 --> 32:35.813
so just pop her around
and the money's yours.

32:38.448 --> 32:40.815
(grunting)

32:40.850 --> 32:42.846
Greedy little jackal, aren't you?

32:42.924 --> 32:43.781
Give it to me!

32:43.816 --> 32:45.840
(chuckles) Most certainly will not.

32:45.942 --> 32:47.653
CARVER: Hey, f-forget it!

32:47.749 --> 32:50.240
Just-just give it to him!

32:50.544 --> 32:52.450
I just want her back.

32:52.866 --> 32:54.066
LUCIFER: Fine.

32:55.283 --> 32:56.597
Now bring us the girl.

32:56.633 --> 32:58.144
I'm sorry.

32:58.206 --> 32:59.285
That's not gonna happen.

32:59.377 --> 33:00.496
- (chuckles)
- What?

33:00.531 --> 33:01.569
I will kill you!

33:01.631 --> 33:03.634
Oh, it's gonna happen.

33:04.567 --> 33:05.840
A deal's a deal.

33:05.875 --> 33:08.209
I am not leaving here without Lindsay.

33:08.244 --> 33:10.431
No way.

33:12.248 --> 33:14.193
(sighs) Dearie me.

33:14.239 --> 33:16.839
What is it about you and guns, eh?

33:18.999 --> 33:20.966
(gunshot)

33:22.400 --> 33:23.658
Carver?

33:23.693 --> 33:25.373
Oh, no.

33:28.431 --> 33:30.298
(groans)

33:30.930 --> 33:32.416
Lindsay?

33:32.517 --> 33:34.402
LUCIFER: Wait. <i>Lindsay</i> Lindsay?

33:34.494 --> 33:35.725
Love of your life Lindsay?

33:35.778 --> 33:38.659
Yeah, sorry, but I can't
let you shoot my brother.

33:38.764 --> 33:40.450
What's up, jackass?

33:40.485 --> 33:41.781
I don't understand.

33:41.816 --> 33:43.744
Don't you though?

33:43.834 --> 33:47.238
This foul woman and her backwood
brother played the player.

33:47.273 --> 33:49.308
Lindsay kidnapped herself.

33:49.410 --> 33:51.959
Hell truly hath no fury
like a woman scorned.

33:51.994 --> 33:53.348
You did scorn her, didn't you?

33:53.395 --> 33:55.180
No. No.

33:55.215 --> 33:58.441
For the first time in my life, I didn't.

33:59.156 --> 34:01.256
I loved her.

34:02.270 --> 34:03.510
I love you.

34:03.600 --> 34:05.300
Love me?

34:05.518 --> 34:08.130
Are you kidding? You didn't
even remember my name!

34:08.193 --> 34:09.454
What are you talking about?

34:09.505 --> 34:12.183
I met you two years ago, Carver.

34:12.437 --> 34:14.196
We slept together.

34:14.540 --> 34:15.835
And then you never called again.

34:15.871 --> 34:18.553
Guess I was research for your stupid book.

34:18.632 --> 34:20.308
No, no, that's not possible.

34:20.373 --> 34:22.194
No, I-I would've remembered.

34:22.228 --> 34:23.617
Nope.

34:23.652 --> 34:25.605
I met you at the library.

34:25.683 --> 34:29.128
It's a good place to score desperate babes.

34:29.231 --> 34:31.502
That's in Chapter 11, I believe.

34:31.556 --> 34:32.793
Oh, that's bad.

34:32.828 --> 34:34.762
I was a virgin, Carver.

34:34.853 --> 34:36.170
That's worse. (chuckles)

34:36.205 --> 34:37.574
It was just another night for you,

34:37.648 --> 34:39.946
but it was a big deal for me.

34:39.981 --> 34:43.571
Oh, God, I'm... I am so sorry, Lindsay.

34:43.714 --> 34:45.688
I-I'm different now.

34:45.746 --> 34:48.170
No, I don't think so.

34:48.206 --> 34:49.311
But I am.

34:49.346 --> 34:50.510
Okay, may I speak now?

34:50.545 --> 34:52.404
Because I happen to be
an expert on punishment,

34:52.438 --> 34:54.563
and I'm not sure it fits the crime here.

34:54.599 --> 34:56.661
I mean, Carver made a mistake...

34:56.704 --> 34:58.453
well, several really...

34:58.488 --> 34:59.965
but...

35:00.045 --> 35:01.415
you're different.

35:01.491 --> 35:02.533
He's changed.

35:02.613 --> 35:05.668
Doesn't that mean anything to you?

35:06.044 --> 35:07.874
KEVIN: Shut up.

35:07.990 --> 35:10.223
You shouldn't even be here.

35:10.313 --> 35:11.779
Now you're dead, too.

35:11.861 --> 35:12.927
Shoot them, Linds.

35:13.002 --> 35:15.128
Sorry, can't let you do that, darling.

35:15.195 --> 35:16.968
I mean, I'm indestructible,

35:17.003 --> 35:18.203
but he's off limits as well, I'm afraid.

35:18.269 --> 35:20.627
No, she's right. I-I deserve it.

35:20.733 --> 35:22.275
No, you don't.

35:22.361 --> 35:24.316
Chlamydia, the clap,

35:24.351 --> 35:25.730
raging case of crabs...

35:25.785 --> 35:28.489
that's what you deserve, not death.

35:28.564 --> 35:31.116
(chuckles softly): And you...

35:31.419 --> 35:33.181
...how are you any better?

35:33.231 --> 35:36.570
Why do humans think they can
rectify one evil with another?

35:36.640 --> 35:38.733
(chuckles): I mean, it's
clearly the first time

35:38.804 --> 35:40.448
this reptile has truly loved a woman,

35:40.528 --> 35:41.786
and this is his reward?

35:41.887 --> 35:42.883
KEVIN: Get away from her!

35:42.991 --> 35:45.659
(grunts, coughs)

35:47.427 --> 35:48.158
(gasps)

35:48.193 --> 35:49.022
Oh, God.

35:49.187 --> 35:51.501
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry?

35:51.697 --> 35:53.174
Please don't hurt me.

35:53.209 --> 35:54.408
(sobbing)

35:54.444 --> 35:56.973
Why does everyone say that
before they're punished?

35:57.008 --> 35:58.651
Don't kill me!

35:59.465 --> 36:00.711
Lucifer.

36:01.009 --> 36:01.929
Don't move.

36:01.964 --> 36:04.271
LUCIFER: Detective, you should leave.

36:06.651 --> 36:07.822
Who are you?

36:09.078 --> 36:10.354
(Lindsay crying)

36:12.790 --> 36:15.024
What are you?

36:30.914 --> 36:32.056
CHLOE: Did you do this?

36:32.109 --> 36:34.252
I've been trying to
tell you, I'm the Devil.

36:34.287 --> 36:35.654
(panting)

36:35.817 --> 36:37.496
That's... that's not possible.

36:37.618 --> 36:40.056
I assure you, Detective, it is.

36:40.168 --> 36:42.827
I mean, you've said yourself,
there are things you can't explain.

36:42.955 --> 36:45.164
You need more proof? You've
got the gun. Come on, shoot me.

36:45.199 --> 36:47.032
No.

36:47.199 --> 36:48.467
I can't shoot you.

36:48.520 --> 36:51.436
Sure you can. Go on, give her
a squeeze, we'll be good to go.

36:51.471 --> 36:54.246
- No.
- Just shoot me, Detective!

36:54.312 --> 36:56.956
Please! Because maybe
you'll finally realize...

36:57.108 --> 36:58.908
(casing clatters on floor)

36:59.484 --> 37:01.275
Good for you!

37:01.808 --> 37:03.815
See? Hardly hurts.

37:03.850 --> 37:05.564
- (distant sirens wailing)
- I can't believe...

37:05.599 --> 37:07.723
Gah. Actually, no, it's
hurting a little bit.

37:07.840 --> 37:09.615
It's... Gah! It's hurting a lot.

37:09.748 --> 37:11.590
Son of a bitch, that really hurts!

37:11.625 --> 37:13.091
(sirens wailing, tires screeching)

37:14.594 --> 37:16.027
I'm bleeding.

37:16.063 --> 37:18.063
- You're bleeding.
- I'm bleeding.

37:18.098 --> 37:20.165
Oh, crap, of course you're bleeding.

37:20.200 --> 37:21.418
(indistinct police radio chatter)

37:21.496 --> 37:22.884
God, what have I done?

37:22.923 --> 37:25.315
I don't... I don't bleed. It's... (grunts)

37:27.452 --> 37:28.573
Lucifer,

37:28.608 --> 37:30.323
I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

37:30.358 --> 37:31.713
What does this mean?

37:31.822 --> 37:32.753
Well, it means I shot you.

37:32.813 --> 37:34.624
And I'm an idiot, and I'm sorry.

37:34.699 --> 37:36.547
And I'm in so much trouble.

37:36.621 --> 37:39.308
Ah! It really hurts!

37:39.419 --> 37:41.386
(panting)

37:41.421 --> 37:44.189
(indistinct talking)

37:45.960 --> 37:48.037
What's happening to me?

37:49.763 --> 37:51.896
(siren wails)

37:53.100 --> 37:54.817
(indistinct chatter)

37:54.911 --> 37:58.169
(talking indistinctly)

38:00.607 --> 38:02.540
(talking indistinctly)

38:02.576 --> 38:04.451
(talking, laughing)

38:04.514 --> 38:06.544
Well, speak of the devil.

38:06.580 --> 38:10.281
Mr. Morningstar here was just telling
me everything you did in there.

38:10.317 --> 38:11.812
Right.

38:11.847 --> 38:12.686
Well, Lieutenant...

38:12.721 --> 38:14.614
LUCIFER: I was just telling
your boss if you hadn't acted

38:14.649 --> 38:16.839
in the way that you did, then,

38:17.042 --> 38:18.453
well, all hell would've broke loose.

38:18.530 --> 38:20.318
Isn't that right?

38:21.732 --> 38:22.728
Right.

38:22.763 --> 38:23.862
Mm.

38:25.068 --> 38:26.598
Absolutely. And, um...

38:26.633 --> 38:29.271
But you caught the bad
guys; that's the main thing.

38:29.306 --> 38:32.515
OLIVIA: Again, I'm sorry that you got
caught in the crossfire, Mr. Morningstar.

38:32.593 --> 38:34.749
Oh, it's just a graze. I hardly felt it.

38:34.784 --> 38:35.540
(chuckles)

38:35.575 --> 38:38.483
And call me Lucifer.

38:40.056 --> 38:42.201
Lucifer.

38:42.642 --> 38:44.909
(Olivia chuckles)

38:46.623 --> 38:49.291
Thank you again for all of your help.

38:49.334 --> 38:51.598
You are so welcome.

38:55.762 --> 38:57.896
- Bye, now.
- (chuckles)

39:02.936 --> 39:04.669
I thought you didn't lie.

39:04.704 --> 39:06.137
I don't.

39:07.507 --> 39:10.008
But I don't always tell
the whole truth. (chuckles)

39:10.043 --> 39:12.406
Thank you.

39:13.403 --> 39:15.914
You're welcome.

39:16.107 --> 39:18.357
Come on, I'll drive you home.

39:18.450 --> 39:21.148
I should bloody hope so,
now you've crippled me.

39:21.677 --> 39:22.642
Wuss.

39:22.743 --> 39:25.110
(chuckles)

39:28.538 --> 39:29.838
Thanks, Julia.

39:30.053 --> 39:32.153
Have a good night. Drive safe.

39:39.409 --> 39:40.674
Mommy!

39:40.807 --> 39:42.367
(chuckles): Hey!

39:42.429 --> 39:43.779
What are you doing up?

39:43.865 --> 39:45.543
Can't sleep when you're not home.

39:45.579 --> 39:46.845
Come on, I'll tuck you in.

39:46.880 --> 39:49.393
What's that on your shirt?

39:50.364 --> 39:51.676
Oh.

39:51.760 --> 39:54.594
Um, that's, uh... that's
ketchup from lunch.

39:54.659 --> 39:57.448
Nuh-uh. That's blood, Mom.

39:57.518 --> 39:59.544
Right. You're right.

39:59.622 --> 40:03.965
Well, um... I may have hit someone...

40:04.024 --> 40:04.810
with a bullet.

40:04.845 --> 40:07.780
You shot someone? Again?

40:07.897 --> 40:08.800
Barely.

40:08.835 --> 40:09.767
Who?

40:09.803 --> 40:10.703
It was Lucifer.

40:10.738 --> 40:12.570
- Is he okay?
- He's fine.

40:12.606 --> 40:13.514
It was nothing.

40:13.561 --> 40:16.350
It was, like, a little graze.

40:16.442 --> 40:18.316
Okay.

40:20.644 --> 40:22.078
What, babe?

40:22.188 --> 40:24.471
Remember last week, I
told you that boy Noah

40:24.561 --> 40:27.022
kept throwing French
fries at me at lunchtime?

40:27.057 --> 40:28.839
- Mm-hmm.
- And you said

40:28.903 --> 40:31.570
it actually might mean he likes me?

40:31.605 --> 40:32.334
Yes.

40:32.387 --> 40:35.848
Well, since you <i>shot</i> Lucifer,

40:35.941 --> 40:39.478
it must mean you <i>really</i> like him.

40:39.553 --> 40:42.287
(sighs)

40:42.598 --> 40:45.436
Hmm.

40:45.531 --> 40:47.839
You know, it is bedtime, you little weasel.

40:47.874 --> 40:50.934
- (both laugh)
- You weasel. I'm gonna get you.

40:51.012 --> 40:52.812
Story time! Story time!

40:56.483 --> 40:58.283
(door opens)

40:58.318 --> 40:59.284
(Lucifer groans)

40:59.319 --> 41:02.287
(panting)

41:02.322 --> 41:03.588
I know.

41:03.623 --> 41:04.913
Tough day at the office.

41:04.948 --> 41:05.770
What happened to you?

41:05.805 --> 41:07.666
Oh, you'll never guess.

41:07.860 --> 41:09.293
She shot me.

41:09.794 --> 41:11.043
And I bled.

41:11.129 --> 41:12.143
What?

41:12.256 --> 41:13.109
That's not possible.

41:13.208 --> 41:14.574
I know.

41:14.901 --> 41:16.197
What's causing this?

41:16.275 --> 41:17.618
Is there something you're not telling me?

41:17.653 --> 41:19.474
Don't think about it
too much. It's exciting.

41:19.532 --> 41:21.997
No, it's dangerous.

41:23.109 --> 41:26.811
We've had our fun here,
Lucifer, but this can't happen.

41:26.846 --> 41:28.479
(chuckles)

41:28.515 --> 41:30.982
Tell me we're going home.

41:31.017 --> 41:34.175
On the contrary, Maze.

41:34.927 --> 41:37.055
The fun's just begun.

41:37.090 --> 41:42.090
